    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Indemnification, in simple terms, is a clause where one party agrees to cover the losses or damages of the other party under certain circumstances. It essentially means that if a problem arises because of the work you did, you agree to take financial responsibility for that issue. It's a risk-shifting mechanism in the contract, so it's wise to read carefully what triggers this responsibility.",
