      "role": "user",
      "content": "that sounds terrifying lol. it feels like these hidden liabilities are just waiting to jump out and ruin everything if i make one tiny mistake. are there common ways to phrase this so it's not so one-sided? like how do people actually protect themselves from these kinds of unexpected threats in a contract?",
