      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To make it less one-sided, you can try to narrow the scope of your indemnification obligations. For example, you could ask to limit your indemnification only to claims arising from your *direct* negligence or willful misconduct, not just every possible third-party claim. Another tactic is to ensure the agency also agrees to indemnify *you* for issues related to their own materials or instructions. Always seek to negotiate reciprocity in these liability clauses.",
